President Joe Biden spoke with Amir Sheikh Tamim Bin Hamad Al-Thani of Qatar to express gratitude for Qatar's assistance in securing the release of hostages held by Hamas and the implementation of a humanitarian pause in Gaza. Both leaders pledged to maintain close communication to ensure the successful execution of the agreement and the eventual release of all hostages. They emphasized the importance of safeguarding civilian lives, upholding international humanitarian law, and providing sustained humanitarian aid to Palestinians in Gaza. Biden and Sheikh Tamim also agreed to continue working together to establish a Palestinian state and achieve a durable and sustainable peace in the Middle East.